# PHP & Plugin Conventions

## General
- PHP 8.3; `declare(strict_types=1);` in every PHP file.
- Typed properties and return types; no untyped structures (no equivalent to `any`).

## Plugins (Shopware)
- Namespace = plugin name (e.g. `MyPlugin\`, `MyBaseTheme\`).
- Services in `Resources/config/services.xml`; dependency injection, no static helpers for testable logic.
- CLI: `bin/console` (with DDEV: `ddev exec bin/console`); register commands as services.
- Migrations for DB changes; no manual SQL scripts in the repo.

## Code style
- Follow project code style (ECS/PHPStan); run checks before commit.
- Keep functions short and readable; move logic into services.
